{"file_path": "output/memo-draft.md", "new_string": "The critical variable is Stonemill. The governance documents give Stonemill a **hard, charter-level blocking right** through the Series C separate-class protective provision (§ 4.3.6(b)(i)) — unsatisfiable without Stonemill's consent because it holds 100% of the Series C. The **drag-along provides a viable but contested path** to compel that consent, supportable on the text and DGCL § 218(c) but likely to be challenged in expedited Court of Chancery proceedings; it improves Hargrove's negotiating posture but is not a guarantee. Two items warrant immediate attention outside the normal timeline: (1) the **SensorLink exclusivity** auto-renewal (a possible live conflict with a timing trap that worsens with delay), and (2) a **client-level decision** on whether to negotiate Stonemill's consent or prepare to enforce the drag-along. We will supplement this memo as the requested documents are produced and as the drag-along/protective-provision analysis is finalized.", "old_string": "The critical variable in this deal, as you identified, is Stonemill. The governance documents give Stonemill a **hard, charter-level blocking right** through the Series C separate-class protective provision (§ 4.3.6(b)(i)), which cannot be satisfied without Stonemill's affirmative consent because Stonemill holds 100% of the Series C. The **drag-along provides a viable but contested path** to compel that consent — one that is supportable on the text and on DGCL § 218(c) but that Stonemill will likely challenge, requiring expedited Court of Chancery proceedings. The existence of this path meaningfully improves Hargrove's negotiating posture, but it is not a guarantee.

Two items warrant immediate attention outside the normal memo timeline: (1) the **SensorLink exclusivity** auto-renewal, which may already be a live conflict and which has a timing trap that worsens with delay; and (2) a **client-level decision** on whether to negotiate Stonemill's consent or prepare to enforce the drag-along. We are available to discuss either on an expedited basis.

We will supplement this memo as the requested documents are produced and as the legal analysis of the drag-along/protective-provision question is finalized."}

